<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-21T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="336" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.8810/1159: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at Berlin (<persName type="to">Messersmith</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-21T13:00:00-05:00">October 21, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Roosevelt Steamship Company alleges that pressure is being and
                                has been brought to bear upon German importers and exporters to
                                confine <pb facs="0581" n="477" xml:id="pg_477"/> their shipments to
                                German ships. It is not known whether this pressure, which it is
                                claimed has reached a stage of intimidation, comes from official or
                                party sources. I wish you would discreetly investigate this matter
                                and, if you are able to obtain the necessary concrete information,
                                take it up directly and informally with the appropriate
                                authorities.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>